    "VIII, setting v close to 0 outperforms v = 1 across all prompts and both models, as evidenced by all five evaluated metrics.",
    "This consistent improvement can be attributed to the tighter concentration of the target distribution around zero when v is smaller.",
    "A smaller v encourages the posterior distribution to collapse more severely, leading to more significant disruption in the latent space and, consequently, in the generated images.",
    "Our choice of v = 10 -8 in the main experiments reflects this finding."
